from barbara hlavin subject re patti duke's problem in article writes does anyone have information about the struggles that patti
>duke went through in her personal life with severe mood swings.
>did she have some form of chemical imbalance that triggered
>these problems? i recall that she wrote a book about her troubles.
>does someone have the title of that book? she's published two books about her manic-depressive illness: _call me anna: the autobiography of patty duke_, patty duke and kenneth turan, bantam books 1987 and _a brilliant madness: living with manic-depressive illness_, patty duke and gloria hochman, bantam books 1992 --barbara